Question, EIP-2780 doesn't state what if the gas budget is insufficient for charging the account-creation if the recipient is empty and transaction carries value; or the charge for accessing delegate;

This must be processed after applying the authorization, therefore, not part of IntrinsicCost.

My question is, if gas is not enough, shall we invalidate the entire the transaction as we do in other cases (before entering the call frame)? Or we just interpret it as an exceptional halt.
